00:43:24.564 --> 00:43:26.782
that you--some putative
equilibrium, some candid

00:43:26.782 --> 00:43:28.385
equilibrium,
checking whether it is an

00:43:28.385 --> 00:43:30.500
equilibrium is easy because all
you have to do is check that

00:43:30.500 --> 00:43:33.099
nobody wants to move,
nobody wants to deviate.

00:43:33.099 --> 00:43:35.082
So again, in practice that's
what you're going to end up

00:43:35.082 --> 00:43:37.038
doing in this game,
and it turns out to be very

00:43:37.038 --> 00:43:39.301
easy to guess and check,
which is why you're able to

00:43:39.301 --> 00:43:41.571
find it.
So guess and check is a very

00:43:41.571 --> 00:43:45.389
useful method in these games
where there are lots and lots of

00:43:45.389 --> 00:43:49.064
players,
but not many strategies per

00:43:49.064 --> 00:43:52.809
player, and it works pretty
well.

00:43:52.809 --> 00:43:54.811
Okay, now we've got this game
up on the board,

00:43:54.811 --> 00:43:57.213
I want to spend a while
discussing it because it's kind

00:43:57.213 --> 00:44:00.011
of important.
So, what I want to do now is I

00:44:00.011 --> 00:44:02.870
want to remind us what happened
just now.

00:44:02.870 --> 00:44:06.580
So, what happened just now?
Can we raise the yeses again,

00:44:06.580 --> 00:44:09.532
the invest again.
Raise the not invested,

00:44:09.532 --> 00:44:12.181
