00:45:40.070 --> 00:45:43.823
strategy, is that right?
So, here's an example of a

00:45:43.823 --> 00:45:46.826
third reason from what we
already mentioned last time,

00:45:46.826 --> 00:45:49.773
but a third reason why we might
be interested in Nash

00:45:49.773 --> 00:45:52.588
Equilibria.
There are certain circumstances

00:45:52.588 --> 00:45:56.280
in which play converges in the
natural sense--not in a formal

00:45:56.280 --> 00:45:59.420
sense but in a natural sense--to
an equilibrium.

00:45:59.420 --> 00:46:02.846
With the exception of a few
dogged people who want to pay

00:46:02.846 --> 00:46:05.110
for my lunch,
almost everyone else was

00:46:05.110 --> 00:46:12.502
converging to an equilibrium.
So play converged fairly

00:46:12.502 --> 00:46:21.289
rapidly to the Nash Equilibrium.
But we discussed there were two

00:46:21.289 --> 00:46:23.925
Nash Equilibria in this game.;
Is one of these Nash

00:46:23.925 --> 00:46:27.446
Equilibria, ignoring me for a
second, is one of these Nash

00:46:27.446 --> 00:46:29.670
Equilibria better than the
other?

00:46:29.670 --> 00:46:32.398
Yeah, clearly the "everyone
investing" Nash Equilibrium is

00:46:32.398 --> 00:46:33.930
the better one,
is that right?

00:46:33.930 --> 00:46:36.302
Everyone agree?
Everyone investing is a better

00:46:36.302 --> 00:46:40.287
Nash Equilibrium for everyone in
the class, than everyone not

00:46:40.287 --> 00:46:43.326
investing, is that correct?
Nevertheless,

00:46:43.326 --> 00:46:47.190
where we were converging in
this case was what?

00:46:47.190 --> 00:46:50.760
Where we're converging was the
bad equilibrium.

00:46:50.760 --> 00:46:53.924
We were converging rapidly to a
very bad equilibrium,

00:46:53.924 --> 00:46:56.420
an equilibrium which no one
gets anything,

00:46:56.420 --> 00:46:59.220
which all that money is left on
the table.

00:46:59.220 --> 00:47:02.273
So how can that be?
How did we converge to this bad

00:47:02.273 --> 00:47:04.471
equilibrium?
To be a bit more formal,

00:47:04.471 --> 00:47:07.307
the bad equilibrium and no
invest equilibrium here,

00:47:07.307 --> 00:47:10.369
is pareto dominated by
the good equilibrium.

00:47:10.369 --> 00:47:13.991
Everybody is strictly better
off at the good equilibrium than

00:47:13.991 --> 00:47:17.168
the bad equilibrium.
It pareto dominates,

00:47:17.168 --> 00:47:21.070
to use an expression you
probably learned in 150 or 115.

00:47:21.070 --> 00:47:22.940
Nevertheless,
we're going to the bad one;

00:47:22.940 --> 00:47:24.380
we're heading to the bad
equilibrium.

00:47:24.380 --> 00:47:28.924
Why did we end up going to the
bad equilibrium rather than the

00:47:28.924 --> 00:47:34.579
good equilibrium?
