00:48:40.205 --> 00:48:43.820
other way and converged up to
the good equilibrium.

00:48:43.820 --> 00:48:46.774
Does that make sense?
So people figured out that

00:48:46.774 --> 00:48:49.461
they--people who didn't invest
the first time--actually they

00:48:49.461 --> 00:48:52.239
played the best response to the
class, so they stayed put.

00:48:52.239 --> 00:48:54.458
And those of you did invest,
a lot of you started not

00:48:54.458 --> 00:48:56.847
investing as you caught up in
this spiral downward and we

00:48:56.847 --> 00:48:59.701
ended up not investing.
But had we started off above

00:48:59.701 --> 00:49:02.800
the critical threshold,
the threshold here is 90%,

00:49:02.800 --> 00:49:04.689
and had you made money the
first time around,

00:49:04.689 --> 00:49:07.094
then it would have been the
non-investors that would have

00:49:07.094 --> 00:49:09.412
regretted that choice and they
might have switched into

00:49:09.412 --> 00:49:11.198
investing,
and we might have--I'm not

00:49:11.198 --> 00:49:13.100
saying necessarily,
