00:51:29.670 --> 00:51:30.610
Professor Ben Polak:
Good;

00:51:30.610 --> 00:51:33.071
so in Prisoner's Dilemma
playing Î¬

00:51:33.071 --> 00:51:36.815
was always a best response.
What led us to the bad outcome

00:51:36.815 --> 00:51:40.610
in Prisoner's Dilemma was that
Î¬, the defense strategy,

00:51:40.610 --> 00:51:43.863
the non-cooperative strategy,
