00:52:43.370 --> 00:52:47.565
Why is it a coordination game?
Because you'd like everyone in

00:52:47.565 --> 00:52:51.960
the class to coordinate their
responses on invest.

00:52:51.960 --> 00:52:54.962
In fact, if they did that,
they all would be happy and no

00:52:54.962 --> 00:52:58.180
one would have an incentive to
defect and there would in fact

00:52:58.180 --> 00:53:00.206
be an equilibrium.
But unfortunately,

00:53:00.206 --> 00:53:02.230
quite often,
we fail to have coordination.

00:53:02.230 --> 00:53:05.245
Either everyone plays
non-invest or,

00:53:05.245 --> 00:53:10.242
as happened the first time in
class, we get some split with

00:53:10.242 --> 00:53:14.309
people losing money.
So, I claim that actually this

00:53:14.309 --> 00:53:16.909
is not a rare thing in society
at all.

00:53:16.909 --> 00:53:19.659
There are lots of coordination
problems in society.

00:53:19.659 --> 00:53:22.550
There are lots of things that
look like coordination games.

00:53:22.550 --> 00:53:26.182
And often, in coordination
games bad outcomes result and I

00:53:26.182 --> 00:53:30.070
want to spend most of the rest
of today talking about that,

00:53:30.070 --> 00:53:33.562
because I think it's important,
whether you're an economist or

00:53:33.562 --> 00:53:35.909
whatever, so let's talk about it
a bit.

00:53:35.909 --> 00:53:38.753
What else has the structure of
a coordination game,

00:53:38.753 --> 00:53:41.711
and therefore can have the
outcome that people can be

00:53:41.711 --> 00:53:44.840
uncoordinated or can coordinate
in the wrong place,

00:53:44.840 --> 00:53:47.610
and you end up with a bad
equilibrium?

00:53:47.610 --> 00:53:51.480
What else looks like that?
